The paper discusses a method for learning non-differentiable parameters of large supervised models using Evolution Strategies (ES) and hybrid methods. This work is related to machine learning and optimization, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper deals with supervised learning and proposes a new method for training large models. The second likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper uses Evolution Strategies, which is an optimization algorithm inspired by natural evolution. The third likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper proposes a new method for training models that can be applied to various AI tasks. The fourth likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as the paper presents results on image classification tasks such as MNIST and CIFAR-10. The fifth likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), as the paper also presents results on a recurrent model for text-to-speech.
